In scenarios 2â5, the set of available prognostic pre-treatment variables for the interim and final analyses is incomplete and statistical assumptions for inference in ECTs are therefore violated. In these scenarios, the ECT design performed worse than the HT and RCT designs. For instance, in scenarios 2 and 4, without a positive treatment effect, 71% (>99%) of the generated ECTs reported a false positive result (type I error), compared to 5â8% for the HT design and 5% for the RCT design. Moreover, in scenario 3, the power of the ECT design declined to 12% compared to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
